{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1922A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1922A"},"text":"§ 1922A.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Legacy supplemental service disabled veterans’ insurance for totally disabled veterans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1922A/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any person insured under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1922/a"},"text":"section 1922(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" who qualifies for a waiver of premiums under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1912"},"text":"section 1912 of this title","children":[],"tail":" is eligible, as provided in this section, for supplemental insurance in an amount not to exceed $30,000."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1922A/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" To qualify for supplemental insurance under this section a person must file with the Secretary an application for such insurance. Such application must be filed not later than (1) ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1993","children":[],"tail":", or (2) the end of the one-year period beginning on the date on which the Secretary notifies the person that the person is entitled to a waiver of premiums under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1912"},"text":"section 1912 of this title","children":[],"tail":", whichever is later. The Secretary may not accept any such application after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2022","children":[],"tail":". Except as provided by section 1922(d)(2)(B), a veteran may not have supplemental insurance under this section and be insured under section 1922B simultaneously."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1922A/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Supplemental insurance granted under this section shall be granted upon the same terms and conditions as insurance granted under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1922/a"},"text":"section 1922(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", except that such insurance may not be granted to a person under this section unless the application is made for such insurance before the person attains 65 years of age."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1922A/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" No waiver of premiums shall be made in the case of any person for supplemental insurance granted under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc31b152f-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/568/tII/s203/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–568, title II, § 203(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4324"},"text":"106 Stat. 4324","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/446/tXII/s1201/f/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–446, title XII, § 1201(f)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4687"},"text":"108 Stat. 4687","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275/tIV/s401/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275, title IV, § 401(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2879"},"text":"124 Stat. 2879","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/tII/s2004/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, title II, § 2004(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4974"},"text":"134 Stat. 4974","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc31b1530-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc31b1531-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc31b1532-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/s2004/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, § 2004(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Legacy supplemental” for “Supplemental” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/s2004/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, § 2004(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “The Secretary may not accept any such application after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2022","children":[],"tail":". Except as provided by section 1922(d)(2)(B), a veteran may not have supplemental insurance under this section and be insured under section 1922B simultaneously.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275","children":[],"tail":" substituted “$30,000” for “$20,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/446"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–446","children":[],"tail":" substituted “insurance. Such application must be filed not later than (1) "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1993","children":[],"tail":", or (2) the end of the one-year period beginning on the date on which the Secretary” for “insurance not later than the end of (1) the one-year period beginning on the first day of the first month following the month in which this section is enacted, or (2) the one-year period beginning on the date that the Department”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc31b1533-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc31b1534-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2010 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275/tIV/s401/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275, title IV, § 401(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2879"},"text